#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""ccost — token and cost statistics (at API list prices) for local Claude Code
and Codex sessions.

Reads JSONL from ~/.claude/projects/ and ~/.codex/sessions/, deduplicates by
message.id (streaming writes several lines per message with growing usage, so we
take the field-wise maximum; resume/fork would otherwise double the numbers) and
prices usage at API rates, including the 1-hour cache (2x vs 1.25x for 5-minute).

  ccost           — interactive TUI (live mode, mouse, tabs, periods)
  ccost gui       — live dashboard in the browser (local server, zero deps)
  ccost app       — same dashboard in a native window
  ccost report    — full text report (also the fallback for pipes/non-tty)
  ccost -r        — same as report
  ccost json      — aggregates as JSON (for scripts)
"""
